CNCP v1 23990
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#6704: Components without a script block (or an empty one) don't get `name` set, so Keep-Alive with `include`doesn't work for them.",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:39.149646+00:00",
  "text": "Components without a script block (or an empty one) don't get `name` set, so Keep-Alive with `include`doesn't work for them.\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.2.37\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://sfc.vuejs.org/#\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1、when i write something to the input box of A component, it works\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/65691266/191195634-601921a5-0f43-484a-88e1-bcb7040fdc7b.png)\r\n\r\n2、toggle to B, click +\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/65691266/191195664-bb9008d5-af84-469e-80c1-934be0dc05f8.png)\r\n\r\n3、toggle to C, write something to the input box\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/65691266/191195680-e9c77164-6f97-4a5e-a4e5-6d9f9a0719d6.png)\r\n\r\nThen click every button, you will find that input box of A component is empty. it should be cached, but not. And other component is cached normal.\r\nThe C component like A component, but script tag that has statment in C component, B component is none.\r\n\r\nWhen you delete <keepAlive> include prop or add something to the A component <script> tag, it works normal\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nA component is cached.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nA component is not cached.\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: compiler",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
